Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with security protocols and attacks. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper proposes a formal model for representing and analyzing Cyber-Physical properties. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper mentions the use of the computational rewriting tool Maude. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with Cyber-Physical systems and their properties. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the probabilistic analysis of the novel attack on Distance Bounding Protocols.
